  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (W-AR-02 adversarial sample)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels per decision record), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). Synthetic adversarial sample targeting W-AR-02: the Output comparison factor carries achievedLevel 1 against requiredLevel 2, a structural shortfall masked by extended qualitative rationale in the decision record.",
